<sec>
<st>
Biography</st>

<p>

He was a close friend of Paul Vario, Jimmy Burke who was his business partner and <airline wordnetid="102690081" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../733/97733.xml">
Lufthansa</link></airline>
 employee <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<unfortunate wordnetid="109630641" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<victim wordnetid="110752093" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../921/6772921.xml">
Robert McMahon</link></causal_agent>
</victim>
</person>
</unfortunate>
</physical_entity>
 who he had been introduced to by Burke. He was a habituate of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../831/10494831.xml">
Robert's Lounge</link> in the early sixties and was involved in hijacking and dealing in swag merchandise with Jimmy Burke and to a lesser degree <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../295/2749295.xml">
Henry Hill</link>. No dates are mentioned but his murder seems to have had occurred in the early 1960's. Remo’s last name was a mystery to Henry Hill and Jimmy Burke’s fellow associates. Remo’s death in reality, mimics the on-screen death of the Morrie Kessler character based on <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<unfortunate wordnetid="109630641" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<principal wordnetid="110474950" confidence="0.8">
